      "reasoning": "After reviewing the session descriptions, several dependencies between events emerge that imply an intended narrative order for the weapon\u2010crafting subplot. First, the session 'VB_TakeSussurSap' is required to acquire the special ingredient (sussur sap/bark) needed for later crafting. In addition, the player must become aware of the special weapon design either by reading the blueprints in 'VB_TakePlans' or by reading the apprentice\u2019s journal in 'VB_TakeJournal'. When the player subsequently reaches 'PAD_ForgeAndBarkCombined', the dialogue checks whether the player has knowledge of the weapon\u2019s design \u2013 a condition that is satisfied by having completed one of those two sessions. From there, the narrative leads to the actual forging process: first by interacting with the forge in 'AD_ForgeWeapon' (where dialogues and checks regarding the recipe occur), and finally to the culminating crafting scene in 'ForgeWeapon'. No other sessions are tightly linked by cause and effect, and none seem inherently mutually exclusive. (Note: Although 'VB_TakePlans' and 'VB_TakeJournal' both provide information on the weapon design, they can be viewed as alternative means of obtaining the same knowledge; hence, they are not flagged as mutually exclusive in this reasoning.)",
